				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Grunge Golem" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Truth or dare in a new jacket where hedonism is encouraged. A fun party game that will confront friends with things they didn't (want to) know about each other.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Willingly or not, they will be the tools of 4 Grunge Gods:&amp;#10;-Bacchos: God of gluttony and the digestive system.&amp;#10;-Eros: God of flirting, passion and romance.&amp;#10;-Ludos: God of naivety, games and fun.&amp;#10;-Spiritos: God of dreams and fears.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Opposing these four is Logos, the sober god of discipline, rules and protector of civilization.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Depending on what space the players land on after a roll, they will get tasks from the Grunge Gods, or be left alone of they are lucky enough to land on a space of Logos. These tasks translate in either small assignments or answering a question truthfully.&amp;#10;Every time a task is completed successfully, that player may discard one of the task cards in his hands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player that has no cards left can become a Grunge Golem, capable of dealing out more assignments to his fellow players, thereby giving them the chance to discard more of their own task cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when only Grunge Golems remain in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Originally this game was released in Belgium in Dutch. Up till now this is the only available version.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
